# Gate — Required Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# Gate reads these from the shell environment (not this file directly).
# Export them in your shell profile or set them in your LaunchAgent.

# GitHub Personal Access Token
# GH_TOKEN is automatically derived from GATE_PAT for subprocess auth.
#
# ── Fine-grained PAT (recommended, partial coverage) ──────────────────
# Repository permissions required:
#   • Metadata ............ Read       (always required)
#   • Contents ............ Read/Write (clone, push fix-senior branches)
#   • Pull requests ....... Read/Write (list, comment, edit labels)
#   • Commit statuses ..... Read/Write (write `gate-review`/`Gate Auto-Fix`
#                                        status; read external statuses
#                                        like Vercel, Netlify, Render, …)
#   • Issues .............. Read/Write (only if you use
#                                        `ESCALATION_REVIEWERS` or issue
#                                        comments — safe to include)
#
# Known limitation: fine-grained PATs CANNOT access the Checks API
# (`GET /repos/:r/commits/:sha/check-runs`). GitHub restricts that API
# to GitHub Apps. Gate detects this on first call, logs one INFO line,
# and silently degrades to statuses-only coverage for the rest of the
# process — see `docs/external-checks.md` → "Fine-grained PAT
# limitation". For Vercel-gated repos this is usually fine. For repos
# that gate on GitHub-Actions / CircleCI / Buildkite job names, see
# the classic-PAT and GitHub-App options below.
#
# ── Classic PAT (full coverage, on deprecation watch) ─────────────────
# Scopes: `repo` (required), `workflow` (only if `fix-senior` ever
# touches `.github/workflows/*.yml`), `read:org`.
# Classic PATs can read check-runs — no PAT-permission gap. GitHub has
# not announced an end-of-life but has stopped adding features. Fine
# for self-hosted bots; rotate yearly.
#
# ── GitHub App installation token (full coverage, proper) ─────────────
# The documented path GitHub points you to for Checks-API access. See
# `docs/external-checks.md` for the migration sketch; not wired into
# `GATE_PAT` today.
GATE_PAT=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Claude CLI authentication token
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# Codex CLI authentication (for fix pipeline — optional if not using auto-fix)
# Preferred: run 'codex login' to authenticate with your ChatGPT account.
# Alternative: set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-... for API key auth.

# ntfy.sh topic for push notifications (optional)
GATE_NTFY_TOPIC=

# Discord webhook URL for notifications (optional)
GATE_DISCORD_WEBHOOK=
